BR_text.BRsummary: Benchmark tool on Chrome Android falsely says "Skipping kernel time, use Chrome +70"
BR_text.BRdescription:
<denchmark-link:https://tensorflow.github.io/tfjs/e2e/benchmarks/>https://tensorflow.github.io/tfjs/e2e/benchmarks/</denchmark-link>
  on Chrome 84 Android 8.1 when I select WebGL (and leave it on mobilenet_v2) seems to behave as if I have a version of Chrome 70 or earlier.

comments_0.comment_text:
<denchmark-link:https://github.com/ToonTalk>@ToonTalk</denchmark-link>
  its working fine on my MAC OS , what device you are using ?

comments_1.comment_text: Nexus 5 Android phone -- yes, it works fine on my Windows laptop too.

comments_2.comment_text: Chrome android doesn't have the query timer aPI, but that's ok, we use a fallback in order to time kernels, So you can ignore above message.

comments_3.comment_text: The message here is misleading. The reason of skipping kernel times is because the browser does not supports  or  extensions, which is not only related to the browser version. I sent a fix here: <denchmark-link:https://github.com/tensorflow/tfjs/pull/3725>#3725</denchmark-link>
